HEADWORD: Pegm
<hw>Pegm</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pegma</ets> a movable stage, Gr. <grk>ph^gma</grk>, orig., a
framework.]</ety> <def>A sort of moving machine employed in the old
pageants.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
